channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at colleges across the US
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities where several schools have called police on protesters, leading to the arrests of hundreds across the country. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Regulators close Philadelphia-based Republic First Bank, first US bank failure this year
item.description: Regulators have closed Republic First Bank, a regional lender operating in Pennsylvania, New Jersey and New York

item.title: Day 8 of Trump New York hush money trial
item.description: Ex-tabloid publisher David Pecker and Donald Trump's former assistant Rhona Graff were among those who testifed Friday in the hush money trial.

item.title: NFL to allow players to wear protective soft-shell helmet covers during games
item.description: The NFL says it will allow players to wear protective soft-shell helmet covers known as Guardian caps during games next season if they choose

item.title: Nuclear Power/IAEA Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Nuclear Power/IAEA Fast Facts and learn more about the International Atomic Energy Agency and nuclear power.

item.title: Sheriff's deputies fatally shoot driver while serving a high-risk drug warrant in Memphis
item.description: Officials say sheriff’s deputies fatally shot a man who sped toward them in a vehicle as they were serving a search warrant in a neighborhood on Friday in Memphis, Tennessee

item.title: Mark David Chapman Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Mark David Chapman Fast Facts and learn more about the life of the man who killed musician John Lennon.

item.title: 1 climber dead, another seriously hurt after 1,000-foot fall on Alaska peak
item.description: Authorities say a climber is dead and another seriously injured after falling about 1,000 feet while on a steep, technical route on Mount Johnson in Alaska’s Denali National Park and Preserve

item.title: Tony Awards Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Fast Facts about the Tony Awards, which honor achievements on Broadway.

item.title: Retired pro wrestler, failed congressional candidate indicted in Vegas murder case
item.description: A retired professional wrestler who failed in bids for Congress from Nevada and Texas has been indicted on a murder charge in the death of an Idaho man during a Halloween Party last year at a Las Vegas Strip hotel
